{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"http://ghost.local:8000","title":"Ghost Docs","description":"Everything you need to know about working with the Ghost professional publishing platform."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Structure","date":"2018-10-01","date_pretty":"01 October, 2018","path":null,"meta_title":"Ghost Handlebars Theme Structure - Documenation","meta_description":"Discover the building blocks of a Handlebars theme in Ghost and start building a custom publication of your own! ðŸ‘»","image":null,"next":{"url":"/api/handlebars-themes/packagejson/","title":"Package.json","description":null},"sidebar":"handlebars","toc":null,"keywords":["structure","handlebars","themes","templates"]},"html":"<p>A Ghost theme contains static HTML templates that make use of helpers to output data from your site, and custom CSS for styling. </p>\n<h2 id=\"structure\"><a href=\"#structure\" aria-label=\"structure permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Structure</h2>\n<p>The recommended file structure for a Ghost theme is:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">File structure</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token keyword\">.</span>\nâ”œâ”€â”€ /assets\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>   â””â”€â”€ /css\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>       â”œâ”€â”€ screen.css\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>   â”œâ”€â”€ /fonts\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>   â”œâ”€â”€ /images\n<span class=\"token operator\">|</span>   â”œâ”€â”€ /js\nâ”œâ”€â”€ default.hbs\nâ”œâ”€â”€ index.hbs <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nâ””â”€â”€ post.hbs <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nâ””â”€â”€ package.json <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>An optional <code class=\"language-text\">/partials</code> directory allows you to use partial templates across your site. This allows you to share blocks of HTML between multiple templates and reduce code duplication. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">File structure</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token keyword\">.</span>\nâ”œâ”€â”€ /assets\n    â”œâ”€â”€ /css\n        â”œâ”€â”€ screen.css\n    â”œâ”€â”€ /fonts\n    â”œâ”€â”€ /images\n    â”œâ”€â”€ /js\nâ”œâ”€â”€ /partials\n    â”œâ”€â”€ list-post.hbs\nâ”œâ”€â”€ default.hbs\nâ”œâ”€â”€ index.hbs <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nâ””â”€â”€ post.hbs <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nâ””â”€â”€ package.json <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>required<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"templates\"><a href=\"#templates\" aria-label=\"templates permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Templates</h3>\n<p>Two template files are required: <code class=\"language-text\">index.hbs</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">post.hbs</code>. All other templates are optional. We <strong>highly</strong> recommended using  a <code class=\"language-text\">default.hbs</code> file as a base layout for your theme. If you have significantly different layouts for different pages or content types, you can use the <a href=\"/concepts/routing/\">dynamic routing</a> configuration layer, or use partials to encapsulate common parts of your theme. </p>\n<p>Theme templates are hierarchical, so one template can extend another template. This prevents base HTML from being repeated. Here are some commonly used theme templates and their uses:</p>\n<h4 id=\"defaulthbs\"><a href=\"#defaulthbs\" aria-label=\"defaulthbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>default.hbs</h4>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">default.hbs</code> is a base template that contains the boring bits of HTML that exist on every page such as <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;html&gt;</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;head&gt;</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;body&gt;</code> as well as the required <code class=\"language-text\">{{ghost_head}}</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">{{ghost_foot}}</code> and any HTML for the header and footer.</p>\n<h4 id=\"indexhbs\"><a href=\"#indexhbs\" aria-label=\"indexhbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>index.hbs</h4>\n<p>This is the standard required template for a list of posts. It is also used if your theme does not have a <code class=\"language-text\">tag.hbs</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">author.hbs</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">index.hbs</code> template. The <code class=\"language-text\">index.hbs</code> template usually extends <code class=\"language-text\">default.hbs</code> and is passed a list of posts using the <code class=\"language-text\">{{#foreach}}</code> helper.</p>\n<h4 id=\"homehbs\"><a href=\"#homehbs\" aria-label=\"homehbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>home.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional template to provide special content for the home page. This template will only be used to render <code class=\"language-text\">/</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"posthbs\"><a href=\"#posthbs\" aria-label=\"posthbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>post.hbs</h4>\n<p>The required template for a single post which extends <code class=\"language-text\">default.hbs</code> and uses the <code class=\"language-text\">{{#post}}</code> helper to output the post details. Custom templates for individual posts can be created using <code class=\"language-text\">post-:slug.hbs</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"pagehbs\"><a href=\"#pagehbs\" aria-label=\"pagehbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>page.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional template for static pages. If this is not specified then <code class=\"language-text\">post.hbs</code> will be used. Custom templates for individual pages can be created using <code class=\"language-text\">page-:slug.hbs</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"custom-template-namehbs\"><a href=\"#custom-template-namehbs\" aria-label=\"custom template namehbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>custom-{{template-name}}.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional custom templates that can be selected in the admin interface on a per-post basis. They can be used for both posts and pages.</p>\n<h4 id=\"taghbs\"><a href=\"#taghbs\" aria-label=\"taghbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>tag.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional template for tag archive pages. If not specifed the <code class=\"language-text\">index.hbs</code> template is used. Custom templates for individual tags can be created using <code class=\"language-text\">tag-:slug</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"authorhbs\"><a href=\"#authorhbs\" aria-label=\"authorhbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>author.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional template for author archive pages. If not specified the <code class=\"language-text\">index.hbs</code> template is used. Custom templates for individual authors can be created using <code class=\"language-text\">author{{slug}}</code>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"privatehbs\"><a href=\"#privatehbs\" aria-label=\"privatehbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>private.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional template for the password form page on password protected publications.</p>\n<h4 id=\"errorhbs\"><a href=\"#errorhbs\" aria-label=\"errorhbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>error.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional theme template for any 404 or 500 errors. If one is not specified Ghost will use the default.</p>\n<h4 id=\"amphbs\"><a href=\"#amphbs\" aria-label=\"amphbs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>amp.hbs</h4>\n<p>An optional theme template for  AMP (<a href=\"https://www.ampproject.org/docs/get_started/about-amp.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Accelerated Mobile Pages</a>). If your theme doesn't provide an <code class=\"language-text\">amp.hbs</code> file, Ghost will use its default.</p>\n<h4 id=\"robotstxt\"><a href=\"#robotstxt\" aria-label=\"robotstxt permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>robots.txt</h4>\n<p>Themes can include a robots.txt which overrides the default robots.txt provided by Ghost.</p>\n<p>The development version of the default theme <a href=\"https://github.com/TryGhost/Casper\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Casper</a> can be used to explore how Ghost themes work, or you can customise Casper and make it your own!</p>\n<h3 id=\"helpers\"><a href=\"#helpers\" aria-label=\"helpers permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Helpers</h3>\n<p>Ghost templates are constructed from HTML and handlebars helpers. There are a few requirements:</p>\n<p>In order for a Ghost theme to work, you must make use of the required helpers: <code class=\"language-text\">{{asset}}</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">{{body_class}}</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">{{post_class}}</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">{{ghost_head}}</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">{{ghost_foot}}</code>.</p>\n<p>See the <a href=\"/api/handlebars-themes/helpers/\">full list of helpers</a>  for more detailed information about specific Handlebars helpers.</p>\n<h3 id=\"contexts\"><a href=\"#contexts\" aria-label=\"contexts permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contexts</h3>\n<p>Each page in a Ghost theme belongs to a <a href=\"/api/handlebars-themes/context/\">context</a> which is determined by the URL. The context will decide what template will be used, what data is available and what is output by the <code class=\"language-text\">{{body_class}}</code> helper. </p>\n<h3 id=\"styling\"><a href=\"#styling\" aria-label=\"styling permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Styling</h3>\n<p>When building themes it is important to consider the scope of classes and IDs to avoid clashes between your main styling and your post styling. IDs are automatically generated for headings and used inside a post, so it's best practice to scope things to a particular part of the page. For example: #themename-my-id is preferrable to #my-id.</p>\n<h3 id=\"development-mode\"><a href=\"#development-mode\" aria-label=\"development mode permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Development mode</h3>\n<p>It is recommended to use a local install to build a custom theme using development mode â€“ review the <a href=\"/install/local/\">local install guide</a> to get started with your own local install for development.</p>\n<p>In production mode, template files are loaded and cached by the server. For any changes in a <code class=\"language-text\">hbs</code> file to be reflected, use the <code class=\"language-text\">ghost restart</code> command.</p>\n<p>Ghost will automatically check for fatal errors when you upload your theme into Ghost admin. For a full validation report during development, use the <a href=\"https://gscan.ghost.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GScan tool</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"summary\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h2>\n<p>You now have a solid understanding of how a Ghost theme is structured and an overview of some of the most common templates. Before diving into the specifics of contexts, helpers and additional features, the next step is to get an overview of the <code class=\"language-text\">package.json</code> file.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/api/handlebars-themes/structure/"},"timeToRead":5,"excerpt":"A Ghost theme contains static HTML templates that make use of helpers to output data from your site, and custom CSS for stylingâ€¦","fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/zhangh/opt/classes/website1/computervisionsite/content/api/v2/handlebars-themes/structure.md"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/api/handlebars-themes/structure/"}}